File: Health Minister Zweli Mkhize. Editor's note: This event will be live at 8pm on #DStv403 and eNCA.com JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Health is set to reveal details of the first phase of COVID-19 inoculations. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize will be addressing the webinar. Do you still have many questions or concerns about the #COVID19 vaccines?
Join the National Department of Health for a public webinar with leading experts who will be addressing prominent questions about the vaccines. #VaccineStrategySA pic.twitter.com/KJJyaHNdk7 Other panellists include Deputy Health Minister Dr Joe Phaahla, Deputy Director-General of Health Dr Anban Pillay, and the Chairperson of the Ministerial Advisory Committee on Vaccines, Professor Barry Schoub. South Africa is expected to start receiving the COVID-19 vaccine at the end of this month.